  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: feafc343992274a48a85506b782026b6, type: 3}
  m_Name: FomoSO 6
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::FomoFirewallSO
  Question: Unknown cryptocurrency jumps 70%.
  Desc: Trading volume suddenly increased.No official announcement exists.
  cmt1: 100x coin!
  cmt2: Don't miss the next Bitcoin!
  cmt3: Last chance!
  CorrectOption: 3
  CorrectWhatHappenDec: You ignored the sudden price spike because there was no official
    news supporting it. Soon after, the cryptocurrency lost most of its gains as
    early buyers sold their positions.
  CorrectLesson: If you don't understand why an asset is rising, it's often safer
    not to invest. Protecting your capital is more important than chasing quick profits.
  WrongWhatHappenDec: You chased the rapidly rising cryptocurrency without verifying
    the reason behind the move. The price quickly reversed, leaving late buyers with
    significant losses.
  WrongLesson: Large unexplained price increases are often driven by speculation.
    Never invest based solely on fear of missing out (FOMO).
  CorrectGraph: {fileID: -1518829292023962400, guid: 4e972c269a7657149b80525797004101, type: 3}
  WrongGraph: {fileID: -3153698903740456764, guid: 4e972c269a7657149b80525797004101, type: 3}
